item.title: Project Blog Post
item.description: Link to project 1 Link to google Introduction I used the HW 6 example for the mosquito weight for the Aedes aegypti species. I chose to upload the vector of mosquito weights onto python, assigning the objects as “females” and “males” accordingly. I also calculated the mean of these weights through python. Next, I reticulated this vector into R. I then had to converted the python objects into numeric R objects since I believe the orginial object were being interpreted as factors.
